namespace kindergarten_garden {

std::vector<std::string> plants(const std::string& diagram, const std::string& student) {
    // List of children in order
    const std::array<std::string, 12> children = {
        "Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "David", "Eve", "Fred",
        "Ginny", "Harriet", "Ileana", "Joseph", "Kincaid", "Larry"
    };
    
    // Find the index of the student
    auto it = std::find(children.begin(), children.end(), student);
    std::int32_t index = static_cast<std::int32_t>(it - children.begin());
    
    // Split the diagram into rows
    // Find the newline position to split the string
    std::size_t newline_pos = diagram.find('\n');
    if (newline_pos == std::string::npos) {
        // Handle error case, but according to the problem, there should always be two rows
        return {};
    }
    
    std::string row1 = diagram.substr(0, newline_pos);
    std::string row2 = diagram.substr(newline_pos + 1);
    
    // Get the plants for the child
    std::vector<std::string> result;
    
    // For each plant code, map to full name
    // Calculate indices
    std::int32_t pos1 = 2 * index;
    std::int32_t pos2 = 2 * index + 1;
    
    // Process first row
    if (row1.length() > static_cast<std::size_t>(pos1)) {
        switch (row1[pos1]) {
            case 'G': result.emplace_back("grass"); break;
            case 'C': result.emplace_back("clover"); break;
            case 'R': result.emplace_back("radishes"); break;
            case 'V': result.emplace_back("violets"); break;
            default: break;
        }
    }
    if (row1.length() > static_cast<std::size_t>(pos2)) {
        switch (row1[pos2]) {
            case 'G': result.emplace_back("grass"); break;
            case 'C': result.emplace_back("clover"); break;
            case 'R': result.emplace_back("radishes"); break;
            case 'V': result.emplace_back("violets"); break;
            default: break;
        }
    }
    
    // Process second row
    if (row2.length() > static_cast<std::size_t>(pos1)) {
        switch (row2[pos1]) {
            case 'G': result.emplace_back("grass"); break;
            case 'C': result.emplace_back("clover"); break;
            case 'R': result.emplace_back("radishes"); break;
            case 'V': result.emplace_back("violets"); break;
            default: break;
        }
    }
    if (row2.length() > static_cast<std::size_t>(pos2)) {
        switch (row2[pos2]) {
            case 'G': result.emplace_back("grass"); break;
            case 'C': result.emplace_back("clover"); break;
            case 'R': result.emplace_back("radishes"); break;
            case 'V': result.emplace_back("violets"); break;
            default: break;
        }
    }
    
    return result;
}
